<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="503" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,662,686]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">Remarks.</emphasis>
The leafhopper genus 
<taxonomicName box="[588,697,662,686]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[588,697,662,686]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">Balclutha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is cosmopolitan and a taxonomically very difficult group. The genus was adequately described in the Pacific and the Oriental Regions by Knight (
<number box="[1114,1172,697,721]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" value="1987.0">1987</number>
) and Webb &amp; Vilbaste (
<number box="[159,220,733,757]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" value="1994.0">1994</number>
). The character of the pregenital sternite was first used to readily distinguish the species by Webb &amp; Vilbaste (
<number box="[159,217,769,793]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" value="1994.0">1994</number>
) and who successfully differentiated some similar species based on females. Further study of the females of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,260,806,830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,260,806,830]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">Balclutha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed to detect more characters to distinguish species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
